{"title_page": "Arganil (parish)", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name      = Arganil \n|image_skyline      = \n|image_caption      = \n|image_flag         =\n|image_shield       = \n|image_location     = \n|region             = [[Centro Region, Portugal|Centro]]\n|CIM                = [[Regi\u00e3o de Coimbra]]\n|district           = [[Coimbra District|Coimbra]]\n|municipality       = [[Arganil]]\n|coordinates        = {{coord|40.218|-8.054|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          = \n|area_total         = 34.11\n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_total   = 12145\n|patron             = \n|area_code          = \n|postal_code        = \n|website            = \n}}\n'''Arganil''' is a town and a parish in [[Arganil]] Municipality, Portugal. The population in 2011 was 12,145,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 34.11&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Parishes of Arganil]]\n\n\n{{Coimbra-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name      = Arganil \n|image_skyline      = \n|image_caption      = \n|image_flag         =\n|image_shield       = \n|image_location     = \n|region             = [[Centro Region, Portugal|Centro]]\n|CIM                = [[Regi\u00e3o de Coimbra]]\n|district           = [[Coimbra District|Coimbra]]\n|municipality       = [[Arganil]]\n|coordinates        = {{coord|40.218|-8.054|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          = \n|area_total         = 34.11\n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_total   = 12145\n|patron             = \n|area_code          = \n|postal_code        = \n|website            = \n}}\n'''Arganil''' is a town and a parish in [[Arganil]] Municipality, Portugal. The population in 2011 was 12,145,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 34.11&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Towns in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Parishes of Arganil]]\n\n\n{{Coimbra-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arganil_(parish)"}
{"title_page": "Arganil", "text_new": "{{for|the civil parish|Arganil (parish)}}\n{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision\n| type            = municipality\n| official_name   = Arganil\n| image_flag      = Pt-agn1.png\n| image_shield    = AGN.png\n| image_skyline   = \n| image_caption   = \n|coordinates             = {{coord|40|13|N|8|03|W|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:100000|display=inline,title}}\n| image_map       = LocalArganil.svg\n|region             = [[Centro Region, Portugal|Centro]]\n|CIM                = [[Regi\u00e3o de Coimbra]]\n|district           = [[Coimbra District|Coimbra]]\n| leader_party            = [[Social Democratic Party (Portugal)|PSD]]\n| leader_name             = [[Ricardo Jo\u00e3o Pereira Alves|Ricardo Alves]]\n| area_total_km2          = 332.84\n| population_total        = 12,145\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| parishes      = 14\n| holiday = September 7\n| website                 = {{url|http://www.cm-arganil.pt/}}\n}}\n'''Arganil''' ({{IPA-pt|\u0250\u027e\u0263\u0250\u02c8nil|-|Pt-pt Arganil FF.ogg}}) is a municipality in [[Coimbra District]] in Portugal. The population in 2011 was 12,145,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 332.84&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThe present mayor is Ricardo Jo\u00e3o Pereira Alves, elected by the [[Social Democratic Party (Portugal)|Social Democratic Party]]. The municipal holiday is September 7.\n\n==Parishes==\nAdministratively, the municipality is divided into 14 civil parishes (''[[freguesia (Portugal)|freguesias]]''):<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, page 552 17|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref>\n* [[Arganil (parish)|Arganil]]\n* Benfeita\n* Celavisa\n* [[Cepos e Teixeira]]\n* Cerdeira e Moura da Serra\n* Coja e Barril de Alva\n* Folques\n* Pi\u00f3d\u00e3o\n* Pomares\n* Pombeiro da Beira\n* S\u00e3o Martinho da Corti\u00e7a\n* Sarzedo\n* Secarias\n* Vila Cova de Alva e Anseriz\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/vitor107/sets/1419526/ Photos from Arganil]\n* [http://arganil.eu/ More infos from Arganil]\n* http://arganil.blogspot.pt/\n\n{{Municipalities of Coimbra}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Municipalities of Portugal]]\n[[Category:Municipalities of Coimbra District]]\n\n\n{{Coimbra-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{for|the civil parish|Arganil (parish)}}\n{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision\n| type            = municipality\n| official_name   = Arganil\n| image_flag      = Pt-agn1.png\n| image_shield    = AGN.png\n| image_skyline   = \n| image_caption   = \n|coordinates             = {{coord|40|13|N|8|03|W|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:100000|display=inline,title}}\n| image_map       = LocalArganil.svg\n|region             = [[Centro Region, Portugal|Centro]]\n|CIM                = [[Regi\u00e3o de Coimbra]]\n|district           = [[Coimbra District|Coimbra]]\n| leader_party            = [[Social Democratic Party (Portugal)|PSD]]\n| leader_name             = [[Ricardo Jo\u00e3o Pereira Alves|Ricardo Alves]]\n| area_total_km2          = 332.84\n| population_total        = 12,145\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| parishes      = 14\n| holiday = September 7\n| website                 = {{url|http://www.cm-arganil.pt/}}\n}}\n'''Arganil''' ({{IPA-pt|\u0250\u027e\u0263\u0250\u02c8nil|-|Pt-pt Arganil FF.ogg}}) is a municipality in [[Coimbra District]] in Portugal. The population in 2011 was 12,145,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 332.84&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThe present mayor is Ricardo Jo\u00e3o Pereira Alves, elected by the [[Social Democratic Party (Portugal)|Social Democratic Party]]. The municipal holiday is September 7.\n\n==Parishes==\nAdministratively, the municipality is divided into 14 civil parishes (''[[freguesia (Portugal)|freguesias]]''):<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, page 552 17|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref>\n* [[Arganil (parish)|Arganil]]\n* Benfeita\n* Celavisa\n* [[Cepos e Teixeira]]\n* Cerdeira e Moura da Serra\n* Coja e Barril de Alva\n* Folques\n* Pi\u00f3d\u00e3o\n* Pomares\n* Pombeiro da Beira\n* S\u00e3o Martinho da Corti\u00e7a\n* Sarzedo\n* Secarias\n* Vila Cova de Alva e Anseriz\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/vitor107/sets/1