{"title_page": "Arez e Amieira do Tejo", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name      = Arez e Amieira do Tejo\n|image_skyline      = \n|image_caption      = \n|image_flag         =\n|image_shield       = \n|image_location     = \n|region             = [[Alentejo]]\n|CIM                = [[Alto Alentejo (intermunicipal community)|Alto Alentejo]]\n|district           = [[Portalegre District|Portalegre]]\n|municipality       = [[Nisa, Portugal|Nisa]]\n|coordinates        = {{coord|39.48|-7.73|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          = \n|area_total         = 158.23\n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_total   = 497\n|patron             = \n|area_code          = \n|postal_code        = \n|website            = \n}}\n'''Arez e Amieira do Tejo''' is a [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] in the municipality of [[Nisa, Portugal|Nisa]], Portugal. It was formed in 2013 by the merger of the former parishes Arez and [[Amieira do Tejo]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, page 552 81|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=29 July 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref> The population in 2011 was 497,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/ngt_server/attachfileu.jsp?look_parentBoui=165404348&att_display=n&att_download=y Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica (INE)], Census 2011 results according to the 2013 administrative division of Portugal</ref> in an area of 158.23&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Parishes of Nisa, Portugal]]\n\n\n{{Portalegre-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name      = Arez e Amieira do Tejo\n|image_skyline      = \n|image_caption      = \n|image_flag         =\n|image_shield       = \n|image_location     = \n|region             = [[Alentejo]]\n|CIM                = [[Alto Alentejo (intermunicipal community)|Alto Alentejo]]\n|district           = [[Portalegre District|Portalegre]]\n|municipality       = [[Nisa, Portugal|Nisa]]\n|coordinates        = {{coord|39.48|-7.73|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          = \n|area_total         = 158.23\n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_total   = 497\n|patron             = \n|area_code          = \n|postal_code        = \n|website            = \n}}\n'''Arez e Amieira do Tejo''' is a [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] in the municipality of [[Nisa, Portugal|Nisa]], Portugal. It was formed in 2013 by the merger of the former parishes Arez and [[Amieira do Tejo]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, page 552 81|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=29 July 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref> The population in 2011 was 497,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/ngt_server/attachfileu.jsp?look_parentBoui=165404348&att_display=n&att_download=y Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica (INE)], Census 2011 results according to the 2013 administrative division of Portugal</ref> in an area of 158.23&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal__