 (song)|Supercharger (song)}}\n{{EngvarB|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = The Spark\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Enter Shikari]]\n| cover      = The_Spark_cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 22 September 2017\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     = {{hlist|Angelio Studios|Muttley Ranch|Radiate Studios}}\n| genre      =\n*[[Electronic rock]]<ref name=\"NME-Beaumont\"/>\n*{{nowrap|[[indie rock]]}}<ref name=NNmag>http://newnoisemagazine.com/review-enter-shikari-spark/</ref>\n*{{nowrap|[[post-punk]]}}<ref name=NNmag/>\n*{{nowrap|[[dance-rock]]}}<ref>https://www.allmusic.com/album/the-spark-mw0003091943</ref>\n*{{nowrap|[[electropop]]}}<ref>https://www.allmusic.com/album/the-spark-mw0003091943</ref>\n*[[grime music|grime]]<ref>https://www.allmusic.com/album/the-spark-mw0003091943</ref>\n| length     = 40:36\n| label      =\n* [[Ambush Reality]]\n* [[PIAS Recordings]]\n| producer   = [[Faultline (musician)|David Kosten]], [[Rou Reynolds]]\n| prev_title = [[Enter Shikari Live at Deezer|Live at Deezer]]\n| prev_year  = 2016\n| next_title = [[Nothing Is True & Everything Is Possible]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = The Spark\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Live Outside\n | single1date = 31 July 2017<ref name=\"Live Outside\">{{cite web|publisher=[[Enter Shikari]]|url=https://www.entershikari.com/posts/thespark|title=THE SPARK - Out 22nd September 2017 - Preorders available now|date=1 August 2017|accessdate=18 September 2017}}</ref>\n | single2     = Rabble Rouser\n | single2date = 13 September 2017<ref name=\"Rabble Rouser\">{{cite web|publisher=[[NME]]|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/enter-shikari-rabble-rouser-video-2140353|title=Rabble Rouser|date=13 September 2017|accessdate=18 September 2017}}</ref>\n | single3     = The Sights\n | single3date = 15 December 2017<ref>https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Enter-Shikari-Releases-The-Sights-from-Top-5-Album-The-Spark-20171031</ref>\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''The Spark''''' is the fifth studio album by English [[rock music|rock]] band [[Enter Shikari]], released on 22 September 2017 through [[Ambush Reality]] and [[PIAS Recordings]]. It was recorded in Northamptonshire in early 2017.\n\n==Background and production==\nFollowing world events in 2016, including [[Brexit]] and the election of [[Donald Trump]], leadman [[Rou Reynolds]] announced on Twitter that he had been suffering from [[generalized anxiety disorder|general anxiety disorder]]. He declared his frustration and newfound inspiration to write what he intended to be the band's most important work.<ref>{{cite web|title=Enter Shikari on Donald Trump, Brexit and using music to fight back|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/enter-shikari-donald-trump-brexit-using-music-fight-back-1855582|publisher=NME|accessdate=18 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nRecording for ''The Spark'' took place at Angelio Studios and Muttley Ranch in England with [[Faultline (musician)|David Kosten]] and Reynolds acting as producers. Sessions were recorded by Kosten and Tim Morris. Additional recording was done by Reynolds at Radiate Studios with assistance from Luke Gibbs. Koston provided additional keyboards and programming to the tracks. In addition, Will Harvey and Augusta Harris contributed violin  and cello, respectively. Koston mixed the album, which was mastered for CD and digital download by [[Bob Ludwig]] at Gateway Mastering and for vinyl by Stuart Hawken at Metropolis.\n\n==Release==\nOn 31 July 2017, the band released a music video for the first single \"Live Outside\".<ref name=\"teamrockrelease\"/> On 13 September 2017, the second single and the music video for \"Rabble Rouser\" was released.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://teamrock.com/news/2017-09-13/watch-enter-shikaris-video-for-new-track-rabble-rouser |title= Watch Enter Shikari's video for new track Rabble Rouser |author= Scott Munro |publisher= [[TeamRock]] |date= 14 September 2017 |accessdate= 22 September 2017}}</ref> The album was released on 22 September 2017 through Ambush Reality and [[PIAS Recordings]].<ref>{{cite web|title=THE SPARK \u2013 Out 22nd September 2017|url=https://www.entershikari.com/posts/thespark|website=Enter Shikari|accessdate=18 September 2017}}</ref> In November and December 2017, the band will support the release of the album with an arena tour of the UK and mainland Europe.<ref name=\"teamrockrelease\">{{cite web|url= http://teamrock.com/news/2017-08-01/enter-shikari-announce-new-album-the-spark |title= Enter Shikari will release their 5th studio album The Spark in September - watch virtual reality-themed video for new track Live Outside |author= Scott Munro |publisher= [[TeamRock]] |date= 1 August 2017 |accessdate= 22 September 2017 }}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| MC = 74/100<ref name=\"meta\">{{cite web|title=Critic Reviews for The Spark|url=https://www.metacritic.com/music/the-spark/enter-shikari/critic-reviews|website=Metacritic|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>\n| rev1 = ''[[Alternative Press (magazine)|Alternative Press]]''\n| rev1Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"meta\"/>\n| rev2 = ''[[Drowned In Sound]]''\n| rev2Score = 8/10<ref>{{cite web|last1=Beardsworth|first1=Luke|title=Album Review: Enter Shikari - The Spark|url=http://drownedinsound.com/releases/20076/reviews/4151363|website=Drowned in Sound|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev3Score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"Guardian-Davies\">{{cite web|last1=Davies|first1=Hannah J.|title=Enter Shikari: The Spark review \u2013 innovative post-hardcore quartet push their boundaries|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2017/sep/21/enter-shikari-the-spark-review-innovative-post-hardcore-quartet-push-their-boundaries|website=The Guardian|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[The Independent]]''\n| rev4Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|last1=O'Connor|first1=Roisin|title=Album reviews: The Killers \u2013 Wonderful Wonderful, The Horrors \u2013 V, Enter Shikari \u2013 The Spark|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/the-killers-wonderful-wonderful-review-album-enter-shikari-the-spark-the-horrors-v-release-reviews-a7959061.html|website=The Independent|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[Kerrang!]]''\n| rev5Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"meta\"/>\n| rev6 = ''[[NME]]''\n| rev6Score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"NME-Beaumont\">{{cite web|last1=Beaumont|first1=Mark|title=Enter Shikari \u2013 \u2018The Spark\u2019 Review|url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/enter-shikari-spark-review|website=NME|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[Sputnikmusic]]''\n| rev7Score = {{rating|4|5|score=3.8/5 stars}}<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rowan5215|title=Review: Enter Shikari - The Spark|url=https://www.sputnikmusic.com/review/74900/Enter-Shikari-The-Spark/|website=Sputnikmusic|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n\n''The Spark'' was met with positive reviews from critics. Metacritic gave the album an aggregated score of 74/100, indicating \"generally favorable reviews\", based on 10 reviews.<ref name=\"meta\"/>\n\nFrancesca Gosling writing for [[The Irish Times]] gave The Spark a positive score of 8/10, summarising that \"Those hoping for a return to the earlier sound may be disappointed, but Enter Shikari's unflinching desire to evolve with every release is something very exciting indeed.\"<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.irishnews.com/arts/2017/09/22/news/album-reviews-fergie-s-double-duchess-a-flawless-fusion-of-hip-hop-and-pop-1141783/ |title= Album Reviews: Fergie's Double Duchess a flawless fusion of hip hop and pop |author= Francesca Gosling |publisher= [[The Irish Times]] |date= 22 September 2017 |accessdate= 22 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n''The Spark'' won the 'Best Album' award at the 2018 [[Kerrang! Awards]].\n\n==Track listing==\nAll lyrics by Rou Reynolds. All music by Enter Shikari.<ref name=SparkBooklet/>\n{{Track listing\n| total_length = \n| title1   = The Spark\n| length1  = 0:47\n| title2   = The Sights\n| length2  = 3:18\n| title3   = Live Outside\n| length3  = 3:37\n| title4   = Take My Country Back\n| length4  = 3:41\n| title5   = Airfield\n| length5  = 4:46\n| title6   = Rabble Rouser\n| length6  = 4:22\n| title7   = Shinrin-yoku\n| length7  = 4:15\n| title8   = Undercover Agents\n| length8  = 4:24\n| title9   = The Revolt of the Atoms\n| length9  = 4:42\n| title10  = An Ode to Lost Jigsaw Pieces (In Two Movements)\n| length10 = 5:55\n| title11  = The Embers\n| length11 = 0:44\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed = yes\n| total_length = \n| headline = Japanese bonus tracks<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/418169/products/1242403/1/|publisher=[[Oricon]]|title=\u30b6\u30fb\u30b9\u30d1\u30fc\u30af  \u30a8\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u30fb\u30b7\u30ab\u30ea|accessdate=24 September 2015}}</ref>\n| title12     = [[Redshift (Enter Shikari song)|Redshift]]\n| length12    = 3:58\n| title13     = Supercharge\n| note13      = feat. [[Big Narstie]]\n| length13    = 3:33\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\nPersonnel per booklet.<ref name=SparkBooklet>{{cite AV media notes|title=The Spark|others=[[Enter Shikari]] |year=2017 |type=Booklet |publisher=[[Ambush Reality]]/[[PIAS Recordings|<nowiki>[PIAS]</nowiki> Play It Again Sam]]|id=PIASR990CDX}}</ref>\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n'''Enter Shikari'''\n* [[Rou Reynolds]] \u2013 lead vocals, keyboards, programming, piano, guitar, trumpet\n* [[Rory Clewlow]] \u2013 lead guitar, vocals, [[mbira]]\n* [[Chris Batten]] \u2013 bass, vocals, organ\n* [[Rob Rolfe]] \u2013 drums, percussion\n\n'''Additional musicians'''\n* [[Faultline (musician)|David Kosten]] \u2013 additional keyboards, programming\n* Will Harvey \u2013 violin\n* Augusta Harris \u2013 cello\n* Julz Baldwin, Eman Kwenortey, Nathan Killham, Jamie Whymark, Alex Cribbs, Jack Goodwin, Lee Jeffrey, Matt Pondell, Arun Chamba, William Tallis, Matt Knowles, Daniel Griffin, Na